The '''''Compact Oxford English Dictionary of Current English''''' is a one-volume [[dictionary]] published by [[Oxford University Press]].  It is intended for a family or upper [[secondary school]] readerships.  The third edition (revised), published in 2008, has 1,264 pages, somewhat smaller than the ''[[Concise Oxford English Dictionary]]'', and is distinct from the "Compact" (single- and two-volume photo-reduced) editions of the multi-volume ''[[Oxford English Dictionary#Compact editions|Oxford English Dictionary]]''. <!--Please edit this page and write whether the dictionary uses the IPA Pronunciation or not.-->

