[[File:Suomalaisen_Sana-Lugun_Coetus.jpg|thumb|180px|''Suomalaisen Sana-Lugun Coetus'']]
'''Suomalaisen Sana-Lugun Coetus''' (1745) by [[Daniel Juslenius]] was the first comprehensive dictionary of the [[Finnish language]]. It contains about 16 000 words of the Finnish language, at the end of which is a Swedish list of words. The dictionary contains a lot of artificial neologisms from the 18th century.

The dictionary was republished in 1917 by Salomon Kreander and Juhana Canstrén and edited by A.V. Koskimies. A facsimile of the dictionary was published in 1968.<ref>[http://www.jyu.fi/fennicum/arvokirjat/sanaluguncoetus.htm Suomalaisen Sana-Lugun Coetus] (Fennicumin arvokirjat) [https://web.archive.org/web/20050214024907/http://www.jyu.fi/fennicum/arvokirjat/sanaluguncoetus.htm archived]</ref>

==Further reading==
